{"annotations": [{"id": ["mesh:D005227"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "fatty acids", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.999180793762207, "span": {"begin": 54, "end": 65}}, {"id": ["mesh:D014280"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "triglycerides", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9950414299964905, "span": {"begin": 119, "end": 132}}, {"id": ["mesh:D013261"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "sterol", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9997159838676453, "span": {"begin": 232, "end": 238}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:7555"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "sterol regulatory element&ndash;binding proteins", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.8650185465812683, "span": {"begin": 232, "end": 280}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:6720"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "SREBP", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9884836673736572, "span": {"begin": 282, "end": 287}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "regulatory elements", "obj": "DNA", "prob": 0.6283105611801147, "span": {"begin": 314, "end": 333}}, {"id": ["mesh:D005227"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "fatty acid", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9989793300628662, "span": {"begin": 381, "end": 391}}, {"id": ["NCBITaxon:10095"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "mice", "obj": "species", "prob": 0.9712694883346558, "span": {"begin": 514, "end": 518}}, {"id": ["mesh:D005227"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "fatty acid", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9981557130813599, "span": {"begin": 589, "end": 599}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:948"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "CD36", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9811362624168396, "span": {"begin": 731, "end": 735}}, {"id": ["NCBITaxon:10095"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "mice", "obj": "species", "prob": 0.9613621830940247, "span": {"begin": 739, "end": 743}}, {"id": ["mesh:D005227"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "fatty acids", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9987229108810425, "span": {"begin": 769, "end": 780}}, {"id": ["mesh:D014280"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "triglyceride", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9950860142707825, "span": {"begin": 795, "end": 807}}], "text": "There is ample evidence outlining how accumulation of fatty acids in the liver results in an increased accumulation of triglycerides (Reddy and Rao 2006; Angrish et al. 2016; Ipsen et al. 2018).&nbsp; For example, overexpression of sterol regulatory element&ndash;binding proteins (SREBP), which is one of the key regulatory elements in lipid synthesis, resulted in an increase in fatty acid synthesis and an accumulation of TG species in the liver (Horton et al. 2002).&nbsp; Selen et al. (2021) demonstrate that mice with a KO in a key gene involved in &beta;-oxidation showed increased fatty acid accumulation and increased TG content when fed a high-fate diet.&nbsp; Finally, Koonen et al. (2007) showed that overexpression of CD36 in mice resulted in an influx of fatty acids and increased triglyceride levels.", "timestamp": "Mon Jun 08 16:13:28 +0000 2026"}